# Allowlist for tools/check-bb-no-direct-fetch.sh
# Paths are repo-relative; the scanner rejects exact-match files only.
# Lines beginning with `#` are comments; blank lines are ignored.
#
# cycle-104 sprint-3 T3.3: BB skill resources MUST NOT contain raw-HTTP
# primitives (fetch / https.request / undici / node:http(s) imports) —
# all LLM-provider calls funnel through ChevalDelegateAdapter and into
# the cheval Python substrate. Exempt entries here belong to files that
# either:
#   (a) genuinely need a non-LLM HTTP path (e.g., GitHub API for issue/PR
#       hygiene — not a model call), OR
#   (b) carry the pattern in comments / type annotations only, and the
#       per-line suppression marker would be more noise than signal.
#
# Adding an entry here is a reviewer-visible choice — keep the list small.

# GitHub API helper. Not an LLM provider; uses Node fetch against
# api.github.com for PR / issue metadata. Exempt is intentional.
.claude/skills/bridgebuilder-review/resources/github-cli.ts
